ISIS has announced plans to open a school of nursing in its de facto capital Raqqa . 
  Militants have announced that all nurses working in the area must speak fluent English . 
  The NHS does not yet have English language checks for all nurses in areas under their control . 
  ISIS has also disclosed entry requirements for prospective medical workers . 
  Applicants must be 25 years of age and must speak English . 
  They must also be willing to work anywhere in ISIS-held territory . 
 